00:58:53.580 --> 00:58:55.750
So we're going to get a
gathering of specialists

00:58:55.750 --> 00:58:57.840
in trauma and we're
going to build something

00:58:57.840 --> 00:59:03.160
that sits on your platform that
they can talk to and grow with.

00:59:03.160 --> 00:59:06.697
That's the crazy thing that's
going on with Sidekicks.

00:59:06.697 --> 00:59:09.280
I've been yakking too much here
Can we get a couple questions?

00:59:09.280 --> 00:59:11.564
s still have five
minutes at least.

00:59:11.564 --> 00:59:12.980
AUDIENCE: And
actually, a question

00:59:12.980 --> 00:59:14.810
related to that
because both of you

00:59:14.810 --> 00:59:16.601
may have interesting
perspectives to share,

00:59:16.601 --> 00:59:20.170
but I'm really
curious what companies

00:59:20.170 --> 00:59:22.242
can do for employees
because I know

00:59:22.242 --> 00:59:24.200
this is specific to our
world, and I'm in POps.

00:59:24.200 --> 00:59:26.600
But I have the
experience that I have

00:59:26.600 --> 00:59:28.460
a feeling there are
a lot of folks here

00:59:28.460 --> 00:59:31.030
who would benefit from
an environment that's

00:59:31.030 --> 00:59:34.339
more receptive to
their special talents.

00:59:34.339 --> 00:59:35.630
So what can we do as a company?

00:59:35.630 --> 00:59:37.090
I'm really curious.

00:59:37.090 --> 00:59:39.720
RON SUSKIND: It's
a time of change.

00:59:39.720 --> 00:59:41.630
People are seeing
that differently abled

00:59:41.630 --> 00:59:43.810
is not just a PC term.

00:59:43.810 --> 00:59:47.900
It's a term that's actually
more reflective of what is true.

00:59:47.900 --> 00:59:52.400
So I think part of it is, again,
changing the wider populations,

00:59:52.400 --> 00:59:56.990
whether in the workplace or
beyond it, to say, OK, well,

00:59:56.990 --> 01:00:01.220
this is just a wide gap
of deficits and strengths.

01:00:01.220 --> 01:00:02.600
I'm 50-50.

01:00:02.600 --> 01:00:05.070
Owen's 30-70.

01:00:05.070 --> 01:00:08.690
So it means that you've got to
place both the 30 and the 70

01:00:08.690 --> 01:00:14.403
in your model, to say, yeah, I
know we support him on the 30.

01:00:14.403 --> 01:00:15.760
Oh, yeah, that's hard.

01:00:15.760 --> 01:00:17.180
He needs to take breaks.

01:00:17.180 --> 01:00:18.705
And he needs the
lighting changed.

01:00:18.705 --> 01:00:20.425
He's got to work at home some.

01:00:20.425 --> 01:00:22.050
But I think the key
to that and the way

01:00:22.050 --> 01:00:24.405
human beings are and the way
enlightened self-interest

01:00:24.405 --> 01:00:26.530
works-- and that's the only
thing that really makes

01:00:26.530 --> 01:00:29.550
the world turn, for
better or for worse--

01:00:29.550 --> 01:00:33.820
is to prize the 70 as it is.

01:00:33.820 --> 01:00:35.560
A friend of mine at
Harvard-- I teach

01:00:35.560 --> 01:00:37.744
a class called Public
Narrative and Justice

01:00:37.744 --> 01:00:38.660
at Harvard Law School.

01:00:38.660 --> 01:00:40.035
And I have a lot
of buddies there

01:00:40.035 --> 01:00:41.642
and this guy,
Howard Gardner, who

01:00:41.642 --> 01:00:44.100
is the multiple intelligences
guy, so I've known for years.

01:00:44.100 --> 01:00:45.164
He's an amazing guy.

01:00:45.164 --> 01:00:46.580
At one point, I'm
like, Howard, it

01:00:46.580 --> 01:00:49.230
would've been great if
we'd built yardsticks

01:00:49.230 --> 01:00:52.070
for the other seven, eight
kinds of intelligences

01:00:52.070 --> 01:00:55.170
other than just analytical,
cognitive, which is the winning

01:00:55.170 --> 01:00:56.366
yardstick for everything.

01:00:56.366 --> 01:00:58.320
He's like, yeah,
that would be great.

01:00:58.320 --> 01:01:00.050
It's hard to do first.

01:01:00.050 --> 01:01:02.460
But maybe now, we
can start doing

01:01:02.460 --> 01:01:06.180
that because Owen does
certain things four

01:01:06.180 --> 01:01:08.990
and five times better than me.

01:01:08.990 --> 01:01:10.330
He should be measured on that.

01:01:10.330 --> 01:01:12.020
And me too.

01:01:12.020 --> 01:01:13.480
And I teach at
Harvard Law School.

01:01:13.480 --> 01:01:14.130
OK?

01:01:14.130 --> 01:01:17.940
He should get credit for
being a four x of me.

01:01:17.940 --> 01:01:21.370
That's how we start to
see them as they all are,

01:01:21.370 --> 01:01:24.240
prize them in the workplace,
support them as part

01:01:24.240 --> 01:01:27.280
of a larger corporate purpose.

01:01:27.280 --> 01:01:28.910
I mean, just a
little funny story

01:01:28.910 --> 01:01:30.210
that says it so powerfully.

01:01:30.210 --> 01:01:33.710
So I gave a speech at this
brain conference in Tel Aviv.

01:01:33.710 --> 01:01:35.382
And it was a great.

01:01:35.382 --> 01:01:36.340
Shimon Peres was there.

01:01:36.340 --> 01:01:37.650
It was really exciting.

01:01:37.650 --> 01:01:38.920
And so I talk about all this.

01:01:38.920 --> 01:01:41.202
And a guy walks up to me
from Israeli intelligence.

01:01:41.202 --> 01:01:45.050
Now, I wrote a book in 2006,
one of those big door stops

01:01:45.050 --> 01:01:47.020
called "The One Percent
Doctrine" about the war

01:01:47.020 --> 01:01:48.160
on terror.

01:01:48.160 --> 01:01:49.920
And say his name's Avi.

01:01:49.920 --> 01:01:50.620
OK.

01:01:50.620 --> 01:01:52.578
And I'm like Avi, how
are you? [ISRAELI ACCENT]

01:01:52.578 --> 01:01:54.200
Hey, Ron, it's nice to see you.

01:01:54.200 --> 01:01:55.940
I heard you were
coming to Tel Aviv.

01:01:55.940 --> 01:01:56.790
I said, yeah, yeah.

01:01:56.790 --> 01:01:57.855
We loved the last book.

01:01:57.855 --> 01:02:00.230
I said, you mean "The One
Percent Doctrine" on terrorism.

01:02:00.230 --> 01:02:02.190
No, no, the one about your son.

01:02:02.190 --> 01:02:03.022
Really?

01:02:03.022 --> 01:02:08.180
Yeah, yeah, we have a division
at Israeli intelligence, 2,000

01:02:08.180 --> 01:02:10.350
autistic spectrum young adults.

01:02:10.350 --> 01:02:13.470
They see patterns in
the data we cannot see.

01:02:13.470 --> 01:02:15.140
They're our secret weapon.

01:02:15.140 --> 01:02:16.611
They keep Israel safe!

01:02:16.611 --> 01:02:19.260
I go, oh, my god!

01:02:19.260 --> 01:02:21.290
And I'm like, so they
want to watch movies, let

01:02:21.290 --> 01:02:22.630
them watch movies.

01:02:22.630 --> 01:02:25.300
And I love that
story because it's

01:02:25.300 --> 01:02:28.010
someone under
duress, the Israelis,

01:02:28.010 --> 01:02:31.570
seeing things with clarity,
as the Israelis will.

01:02:31.570 --> 01:02:35.330
And that feels like
the future to me.

01:02:35.330 --> 01:02:36.980
Once you start
seeing it that way,

01:02:36.980 --> 01:02:39.980
you say, I want 10 of them, 20.

01:02:39.980 --> 01:02:41.460
And what's the
special skill here?

01:02:41.460 --> 01:02:42.876
Oh, this is-- can
we measure that?

01:02:42.876 --> 01:02:44.830
Oh, that's fabulous.

01:02:44.830 --> 01:02:47.440
The other part of
it though, it's

01:02:47.440 --> 01:02:51.460
not even the big muscle in
terms of some of that heightened

01:02:51.460 --> 01:02:52.700
ability.

01:02:52.700 --> 01:02:55.500
It's also the social supports.

01:02:55.500 --> 01:02:57.260
And I'll tell you--
and every parent-- I

01:02:57.260 --> 01:03:00.230
know Eileen feels this way.

01:03:00.230 --> 01:03:03.750
And certainly Paulette
knows this in her life--

01:03:03.750 --> 01:03:06.790
is that when there's a person
who's different, whether it's

01:03:06.790 --> 01:03:09.020
a spectrum person
or any person who's

01:03:09.020 --> 01:03:13.250
neurodiverse among
neurotypicals,

01:03:13.250 --> 01:03:15.830
they make us all better.

01:03:15.830 --> 01:03:19.900
They just do because they
call the same question

01:03:19.900 --> 01:03:23.430
that Owen called in our family.

01:03:23.430 --> 01:03:26.750
I mean, I could go
survey 20 businesses.

01:03:26.750 --> 01:03:28.150
How's the workplace atmosphere?

01:03:28.150 --> 01:03:29.880
How do they treat employees?

01:03:29.880 --> 01:03:31.220
How do they treat customers?

01:03:31.220 --> 01:03:33.390
And then I could plant
a spectrum person

01:03:33.390 --> 01:03:36.550
in each business,
re-survey them.

01:03:36.550 --> 01:03:38.376
Everything will improve.

01:03:38.376 --> 01:03:41.349
They'll treat each other
better in the workplace.

01:03:41.349 --> 01:03:43.390
They'll treat customers
better when they come in.

01:03:43.390 --> 01:03:46.180
Customers will come
to see the person.

01:03:46.180 --> 01:03:48.910
It's their favorite employee.

01:03:48.910 --> 01:03:53.740
That's complex, hard to
measure, but absolutely true.

01:03:53.740 --> 01:03:56.680
So the question is,
how do we get there?

01:03:56.680 --> 01:03:59.047
And I think
everyone's getting it.

01:03:59.047 --> 01:04:00.880
And we're just a part
of it, all of us here.

01:04:00.880 --> 01:04:03.457
And if it's going to happen,
it's going to happen here.

01:04:03.457 --> 01:04:04.040
You know that.

01:04:04.040 --> 01:04:06.720
This is Google, for Christ sake.

01:04:06.720 --> 01:04:12.640
You guys are grasping
the reins of the future

01:04:12.640 --> 01:04:15.850
in terms of especially data.

01:04:15.850 --> 01:04:17.310
I'm a journalist.

01:04:17.310 --> 01:04:18.633
We had no data forever.

01:04:18.633 --> 01:04:20.730
I never even knew
who read the stories

01:04:20.730 --> 01:04:22.560
I wrote in the "Journal."

01:04:22.560 --> 01:04:27.750
You've got data which reveals
us as to who we really are.

01:04:27.750 --> 01:04:31.100
It's going to happen at a place
like this, here or Facebook

01:04:31.100 --> 01:04:33.850
or Microsoft or one
of the big shops

01:04:33.850 --> 01:04:36.540
because people say OK,
we have the horsepower

01:04:36.540 --> 01:04:39.250
and by virtue of the fact
that we are embracing

01:04:39.250 --> 01:04:42.530
neurodiverse people
who are stars

01:04:42.530 --> 01:04:47.560
and are valued members of
our teams, we're changing.

01:04:47.560 --> 01:04:50.140
And we're seeing it.

01:04:50.140 --> 01:04:52.390
And now we know what to do.

01:04:52.390 --> 01:04:54.490
SPEAKER: So on that
powerful note, Ron,

01:04:54.490 --> 01:04:57.910
thank you for the
storytelling, the inspiration,

01:04:57.910 --> 01:05:00.010
for the book and the movie.

